Author: Oracle Component Name: JJKM Informix Simple Component Version: 11.1.2.3 Compatibility: ODI 11.1.2.1 and above
Description: - Journalizing Knowledge Module - This JKM provides simple journalizing procedures on Informix tables - The following objects are created: - Subscribers central table - Journal table - Trigger on the journalized table that tracks the data changes in the Journal table - Views for selecting data
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module creates triggers on your source tables. Be sure to validate the scalability of your applications before releasing your developments in your production systems.

import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang
# Connect to the Source Database ie the one that hosts the journalized tables myCon = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("SRC")
# Create the list of Subscribers for a CDC Set lstSbs = [] <%= odiRef.getSubscriberList("" , "lstSbs.append('[SUBSCRIBER]')", "\n", "") %>
Alter subscribers table for V3 comp

alter table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> add ( JRN_ROW_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> default null, JRN_DATA_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> default null, JRN_COUNT_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> default null )

create table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> ( JRN_TNAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "150")%> not null, JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "50")%> not null, JRN_REFDATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE")%> default null, JRN_ROW_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> default null, JRN_DATA_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> default null, JRN_COUNT_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "255")%> default null, primary key (JRN_TNAME, JRN_SUBSCRIBER) )

insCmd = """ insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> ( JRN_TNAME, JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_REFDATE, JRN_ROW_COUNT, JRN_DATA_CMD, JRN_COUNT_CMD ) values ( /* JRN_TNAME */ '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>', /* JRN_SUBSCRIBER */ ?, /* JRN_REFDATE */ current, /* JRN_ROW_COUNT */ 0, /* JRN_DATA_CMD */ null, /* JRN_COUNT_CMD */ 'update <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> set JRN_ROW_COUNT=(select count(*) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> where JRN_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'') where JRN_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'' and JRN_TNAME=''<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>''' ) """
selCmd = """ select count(*) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> SUBS where SUBS.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? and SUBS.JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """
# Prepare the statements prepInsStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(insCmd) prepSelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(selCmd)
# Execute for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepSelStmt.setString(1, sbs) rs = prepSelStmt.executeQuery() rs.next() nbSubs = rs.getInt(1) if (nbSubs == 0): prepInsStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepInsStmt.executeUpdate()
prepInsStmt.close() prepSelStmt.close()
# Auto Commit mode the updates #myCon.commit()

delCmd = """ delete from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> where JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? """
# Prepare the delete prepDelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(delCmd)
# Execute it for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepDelStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepDelStmt.executeUpdate()
prepDelStmt.close()
# Commit updates myCon.commit()

delCmd = """ delete from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> SUBS where SUBS.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? and SUBS.JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """
# Prepare the delete prepDelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(delCmd)
# Execute it for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepDelStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepDelStmt.executeUpdate()
prepDelStmt.close()
# Auto Commit mode the updates #myCon.commit()

create table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema of the current Data server */ ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "50")%> not null, JRN_CONSUMED <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1")%> default null, JRN_FLAG <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1")%> default null, JRN_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE")%> default null, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] default null", ",\n\t", "", "(PK)")%> )

create view <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_VIEW")%> /* This view is created in the work physical schema of the current Data server */ ( JRN_FLAG, JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "PK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> ) as select case when (<%=odiRef.getColList("(", "TARG.[COL_NAME] is null", " or ", ")", "PK")%>) then 'D' else 'I' end <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_FLAG, JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN.JRN_DATE <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "PK")%>, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN, outer <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "PK")%> and JRN.JRN_DATE = ( select max(L.JRN_DATE) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> L where L.JRN_CONSUMED = '1' and L.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "L.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
				and	", "", "PK")%> )

create view <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_DATA_VIEW")%> /* This view is created in the work physical schema of the current Data server */ ( JRN_FLAG, JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "PK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> ) as select case when (<%=odiRef.getColList("(", "TARG.[COL_NAME] is null", " or ", ")", "PK")%>) then 'D' else 'I' end <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_FLAG, JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN.JRN_DATE <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "PK")%>, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN, outer <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
and	", "", "PK")%> and JRN.JRN_DATE = ( select max(L.JRN_DATE) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> L where L.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "L.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
				and	", "", "PK")%> )

create trigger <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_ITRIGGER")%> insert on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing NEW as NROW for each row ( insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'I', current, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "NROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' /* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */ /* and upper(USER) <> upper('<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>') */ )

create trigger <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_UTRIGGER")%> update on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing NEW as NROW for each row ( insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'I', current, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "NROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' /* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */ /* and upper(USER) <> upper('<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>') */ )

create trigger <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_DTRIGGER")%> delete on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing OLD as OROW for each row ( insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'D', current, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "OROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' /* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */ /* and upper(USER) <> upper('<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>') */ )
